American Teen Sloane Stephens Loses to Ivanovic in U.S. Open Third Round

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-09-04T00:58:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-04/american-teen-sloane-stephens-loses-to-ivanovic-in-u-s-open-third-round.html
Sloane Stephens, the last of the
American teenagers remaining in the U.S. Open, lost tonight in
straight sets to Ana Ivanovic, the 16th seed from  Serbia .  The 18-year-old Stephens lost 6-3, 6-4, joining fellow
American teen Christina McHale as a third-round loser. Madison
Keys and Coco Vandeweghe lost in the second round.  Serena Williams , 29, is the lone American woman who
advanced to the fourth round of the tournament.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  